<TITLE> Cable TV operator killed in Mohammadpur </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 31 (bdnews24.com)A cable TV and internet operator was shot dead by unnamed gunmen at Mohammadpur in the city on Sunday. Syed Sharif, 25, who had internet and cable TV business in Mohammadpur and Lalmatia area, was used to reside in block C at Lalmatia. He was shot in front of Zakir Hossain Road of Mohammadpur at around 11am by gunmen in a motorcycle, said officer-in-charge of Mohammadpur Police Station Shahjahan Kabir. They shot at him indiscriminately leaving three bullets in the chest and abdomen, he said. He was declared dead by the doctors when brought to Dhaka Medical College Hospital. His uncle said he believed the incident was related to business control in the area. Three people were shot at Salimullah Road in Mohammadpur on Friday. bd
